# Development Workflow

## Setup & Installation
- Clone the repository
- Run `npm install` to install dependencies
- Run `npm link` to create a global symlink for development testing

## Testing
- Use Vitest for all tests: `npm test`
- All utility functions should have corresponding tests
- Use mocking (with nock) for external HTTP requests
- Test both success and failure scenarios

## Adding New Template Types
1. Update [bin/cli.js](mdc:bin/cli.js) to add a new command option
2. Ensure the template is available in the GitHub repository specified in [src/config.js](mdc:src/config.js)
3. Update tests to include the new template
4. Update documentation to reference the new template option

## Release Process
1. Bump version in `package.json`
2. Update CHANGELOG if applicable
3. Commit changes with message `"vX.Y.Z"`
4. Create a tag: `git tag vX.Y.Z`
5. Push changes and tags: `git push && git push --tags`
6. Publish to npm: `npm publish`
